What are Food Absorbent Pads?
Food Absorbent Pads are specialized components integrated into food packaging, primarily designed to absorb excess moisture, blood, and other liquids. These pads play a critical role in maintaining product freshness, extending shelf life, enhancing food safety by inhibiting microbial growth, and improving the overall presentation of packaged goods. They are indispensable in the packaging of meat, poultry, seafood, fruits, and vegetables, where controlling exudate is essential for quality preservation.
These pads typically consist of a super-absorbent polymer core sandwiched between layers of non-woven material and a polyethylene film. While traditional pads have faced environmental scrutiny, the industry is rapidly shifting towards biodegradable and compostable alternatives to meet evolving sustainability demands.
